1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,158
When you start the activities, they will follow the same order as this lesson.

2
00:00:05,108 --> 00:00:10,964
First, you do a warm-up: Practise selecting a word by double-clicking or dragging.

3
00:00:10,964 --> 00:00:13,885
Staff can use a large sample word.

4
00:00:13,885 --> 00:00:18,464
Then you answer quick checks, so we know the key words make sense.

5
00:00:18,464 --> 00:00:28,532
Next, you practise the real computer skill: Select one word, copy it with Ctrl + C, click lower on the page and paste with Ctrl + V.

6
00:00:28,532 --> 00:00:34,524
You may also type a short answer, for example: Type the shortcut letter for paste.

7
00:00:34,524 --> 00:00:42,472
At the end, you finish with a stretch or reflection: You copies a name, pastes it twice, then undoes one paste.

8
00:00:42,472 --> 00:00:45,122
Staff only prompts when needed.

9
00:00:45,122 --> 00:00:47,673
Take one activity at a time.

10
00:00:47,673 --> 00:00:52,228
If you need help, ask staff, then try the next step yourself.

